CatDescriptText: Mr. Donald Brundage, 2325 Crockett Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 30, 1958, pg. 3, with question: "Do you think that Negroes make full use of their voting franchise by registering and voting in both the primary and the general election?"  Answer reads: "Yes, I do. I'm from the Third Ward, and on election days there are pretty good turnouts at the polls."
